
[1]pertusion

   PERTU'SION, n. s as z. [L. pertusus, pertundo.]

   1. The act of punching, piercing or thrusting through with a pointed
   instrument.

   The manner of opening a vein in Hippocrates's time, was by stabbing or
   pertusion.

   2. A little hole made by punching; a perforation.
